## Description

## Summary

- Changed default git notes reference from `refs/notes/pr-summary` to `refs/notes/commits` for a more generic and standard naming convention
- Updated source code, configuration, documentation, examples, and tests
- The `notes-ref` parameter remains fully configurable for users who want custom references

## Changes

- **Source code**: Updated defaults in `src/main.py` and `src/git_notes.py`
- **Configuration**: Updated `action.yml` default input value
- **Documentation**: Updated `README.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, and example workflows
- **Tests**: Updated test assertions to reflect new default

## Test plan

- [x] All 100 tests pass with 79% code coverage
- [x] Verified no remaining references to old default in codebase
- [x] Configuration remains fully customizable via `notes-ref` input

## Migration

Users who have already used this action with the old default (`refs/notes/pr-summary`) can continue to use their existing notes by either:
- Explicitly setting `notes-ref: 'refs/notes/pr-summary'` in their workflow
- Or migrating their notes to the new reference with `git notes copy`

